{
  "stem": "11723.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "She went to my other grandmother, who was safely, supposedly, in the sanatorium, and said to her, if you are not going to buy my mother out of the ghetto and put her here with you with the rest of the family, I'm going to denounce you.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my other grandmother put up the money.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this grandmother of mine also went there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And just to show you how things didn't work the way people think they work, at the end of the story you'll see what a mistake my mother made.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And anyway, so now the one grandfather was away already in slave labor.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My uncles were all in slave labor camps, some of them in as far as Russia, some of them just in the vicinity of Budapest.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And now my mother was living with this army officer and my father separately.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And Uncle Regeur we called him, Mr.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Slani, every day went to my mother and carried kosher food to my father.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because my father, although he was modern, he was so religious he didn't want to eat non-kosher.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Now, you know, it wasn't a matter of kosher meat, because there was no kosher meat.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There was no meat, period.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But my mother cooked with kosher dishes and kosher stuff.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that's all my father ate.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this wonderful man risked his life every day bringing food to my father.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Plus, of course, he was the one who went for food shopping and stuff.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And around June-- I'm regressing a little, because around June, we were still living our own place.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I, I never was taken to any ghetto or any place.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Before we were supposed to move out, they already gave us away.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So, in other words, my parents placed us.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
